a small plane crashed and burned monday 
at the end of the runway at fairbanks international airport after 
its engine stalled killing both people aboard a spokesman said 
the twoseat taylorcraft had taken off from the airports gravel 
strip and climbed about 600 feet when the engine stalled around 
420 pm said federal aviation administration spokesman paul 
steucke 
the plane was destroyed by the fire steucke said 
investigators from the faa and the national transportation 
safety board were at the scene but it was too soon to know the 
cause of the crash steucke said 
the victims names were not released the plane was privately 
owned steucke said 
