the vote to 378 percent for vargas llosa with 111 percent blank 
and null votes pop another independent polling firm showed 
fujimori with 56 percent and vargas llosa 365 percent pop put 
blank and null votes at 75 percent 
nearly 10 million peruvians were registered to vote and the law 
requires them to cast ballots 
as the polls opened sunday armored helicopters crisscrossed 
limas skies tanks and troop carriers patrolled the streets of the 
capital home to about 7 million people 
little violence was reported around the country on sunday 
despite threats by the shining path to disrupt the elections 
at least 10 bombs exploded sunday in huancayo a highland 
