<TEXT>
four months ago alberto fujimori was a 
complete newcomer to politics 
those who did know the softspoken 51yearold agricultural 
engineer knew him as the former rector of the respected national 
agrarian university 
now this son of japanese immigrants has astounded peruvians 
with a meteoric rise from obscurity they call it fujimania 
fujimori sold his house car and tractor just to raise campaign 
funds 
he avoided specifics speaking mainly of broad social goals like 
improved health care and revitalized industry 
he sometimes resorted to attentiongetting gimmicks such as 
dressing like a samurai warrior for news photographers 
whatever the formula it worked 
fujimori claimed to be the only candidate truly independent of 
professional politicians but during the campaign he showed 
political skill honed during his years of running a university in a 
country where universities are highly politicized 
fujimori is the oldest of five children the son of a tailor 
from the southern japanese island of kyushu who came to peru in 
1934 to work its coastal cotton plantations 
his father worked at various jobs including an upholstery shop 
he opened in lima the family lost the business during a boycott of 
japanese businesses during world war ii 
in 1960 fujimori earned a degree in agricultural engineering 
from the national agrarian university where he later taught 
mathematics 
he served as the schools rector from 1984 to 1989 he did 
postgraduate work at the university of wisconsin and the 
university of strasburg in france 
fujimori got a peek at the circles of power by serving for two 
years as an agricultural adviser to the outgoing government of 
president alan garcia 
he speaks spanish japanese english french and german 
he describes himself as studious introverted and lacking all 
common vices he says work is his hobby that he devotes 12 to 
13 hours a day to it 
along with their four children fujimori and his wife susana 
higuchi had been running their own threeacre farm before the race 
in his brief time in the political spotlight fujimori has been 
surrounded by controversy critics say the agriculture university 
went into sharp decline under his leadership 
he has been charged with evading taxes on the sale of various 
properties and with illegally benefitting from a landdistribution 
program designed to aid peasants 
in addition his close connections with perus evangelical 
community prompted the countrys roman catholic church to take the 
unusual step of voicing support for the man he defeated celebrated 
novelist mario vargas llosa 
fujimori has been accused of having close ties to the ruling 
aprista party and critics claim he is a trojan horse through 
which garcia will retain power 
the large majority of perus 60000member japanese immigrant 
community supported vargas llosa 
but fujimori was overwhelmingly supported by millions of perus 
poor who account for more than 50 percent this country of 22 
million 
the poor needed an alternative to vargas llosa and the failed 
policies of the present government said jorge castillo of the 
private polling company datum fujimori is a candidate invented 
by the electorate 
fujimori has compared his campaign strategy to the martial arts 
you take advantage of the forces of the other boom boom 
wherever they lead he told the associated press in an interview 
during the campaign slicing his hand through an imaginary brick 
thus he attacked vargas llosas freemarket platform while 
remaining vague about many of his own ideas 
usually dressed in a threepiece suit fujimori appeared stiff 
and serious among potential voters but they warmed to him and his 
promises of discipline and hard work 
he says his political movement called simply change 90 is an 
expression of people who are tired of the old corrupt political 
parties and who just want to work 
