<TEXT>
yitzhak shamir a former guerrilla and spy has 
fought most of his life for one goal a greater israel in 
which jews are safe from what he sees as a hostile world 
this vision will shape shamirs agenda in his fourth term as 
prime minister and leader of israels new rightwing coalition 
government sworn in monday 
shamir has said israel must return not an inch of occupied 
arab land and instead expand jewish settlements in the west bank 
and gaza strip land won from the arabs in the 1967 middle east war 
his likud bloc wants the territories as a security buffer and 
as an intergral part of israel 
the polishborn shamirs emphasis on security has its roots in 
the holocaust in which 6 million jews were killed by the nazis 
shamirs father was betrayed to the nazis by residents of his 
village most of the rest of his family also perished 
shamir 74 has balked at attempts by the united states to prod 
him toward a more conciliatory approach with the palestinians his 
new government calls for uprooting the 30monthold uprising in 
the occupied lands the revolt has claimed 717 palestinian lives 
45 israelis also have died 
standing little more than 5 feet 2 inches tall shamir often 
presents a glowering appearance with his bushy white eyebrows and 
clipped moustache 
he was born yitzhak ysernitzky on oct 15 1915 in ruznoy 
poland as a teenager he joined betar a rightwing zionist 
movement that wanted a jewish state in all of britishmandated 
palestine on both sides of the jordan river 
he immigrated to palestine in 1935 and was quickly drawn into 
the clandestine movement to end british rule and establish the 
state of israel 
he twice escaped from british jails including one getaway from 
a lockup in eritrea in which he rode hundreds of miles through 
sweltering desert heat in the empty tank of a water truck 
shamir eventually became a leader of the militant stern gang 
blamed for the slaying of britains middle east resident minister 
lord moyne and swedish un mediator count folke bernadotte who 
opposed making jerusalem part of israel 
after independence shamir went into business for several 
unhappy years and in 1955 became a parisbased agent for 
mossad israels secret service 
in 1965 after reaching a senior level he retired from the 
intelligence service and managed a rubber factory until his 
predecessor menachem begin the likud founder brought him into 
politics in 1970 
shamir built a career on loyalty to begin serving as knesset 
speaker and foreign minister before taking over as premier in 1983 
when begin suddenly quit 
but he opposed begins main achievement the 1978 camp david 
accords that led to israels 1979 peace treaty with egypt 
shamir said at the time israel could not trust the egyptians he 
now argues that yasser arafat lies when he claims the plo has 
abandoned terrorism and seeks peace with israel 
he also opposed israels withdrawal from lebanon and the labor 
partys attempts with jordans king hussein to arrange an 
international peace conference 
