a launch company monday prepared to 
send up a delta rocket with an indian communications satellite that 
was damaged first in a launch pad accident and then by northern 
californias devastating earthquake 
the unmanned rocket was scheduled to blast off at 152 am 
tuesday from cape canaveral air force station 
abid hussain indias ambassador to the united states said 
monday the satellite will benefit even the poorest and most rural 
of indias 800 million people 
we in india believe that science and technology could be put 
into the service of the people especially those people who have 
been so far behind of some of the advantages of progress said 
abid hussain indias ambassador to the united states 
through this particular satellite we would like to spread 
education and knowledge science and new culture to hundreds and 
thousands of those who have been out of the mainstream of life 
