hills 
with her former husband bernard jacobs mrs willens helped 
prove that a commercial station shunning pop music could thrive 
founded 40 years ago the station is known for broadcasting 
classical music live concerts jazz seminars and documentaries by 
chicago author studs terkel 
she joined radio station woakfm in suburban oak park and in 
1950 married jacobs the stations general manager he changed the 
stations format from pop to classical and the couple presided over 
its success under the new call letters 
the station grew in stature by syndicating programming 
including symphonies and terkels interviews to more than 500 
radio stations 
