bush promised the canadian leader to maintain a liaison and 
consultations as we go through the process the spokesman said 
such a pact would require congressional approval before formal 
negotiations could commence fitzwater said the administration 
envisioned sending the same general kind of legislation to congress 
that set up the uscanada talks 
that measure spelled out a timetable and required congress to 
put the final agreement on a fast track to keep it from getting 
