peres who blamed the prime minister for blocking peace moves and 
said his new government was dangerous for israel 
the government proposed today is a shaky one built on many 
legs of clay peres said its composition its guidelines are 
not bringing peace it has no ability to change no joy of hope it 
is a sad government for its members and a sorrowful government for 
israel 
shamirs last government an uneasy alliance between likud and 
labor collapsed march 15 over labors demands that israel accept a 
us proposal for opening peace talks with palestinians 
the policy guidelines of shamirs new government reject talks 
with the palestine liberation organization and the founding of a 
palestinian state and he made clear he had no intention of giving 
up the west bank and gaza strip where palestinians hope to create 
their state 
