monday marked the 76th birthday of 
british pilot jack mann missing for 13 months now in lebanon 
and his wife lamented the dead silence surrounding his fate 
i am not very bright today theres so little to say said 
sunnie mann who spent her husbands birthday in their modest 
apartment in a seaside residential district of moslem west beirut 
i dont know how he is or how he is surviving i am doing 
nothing today i havent gone out i dont have the courage 
she told the associated press she hoped her husband could find 
the courage to get through his ordeal 
mann was shot down six times by nazi forces as a royal air force 
pilot in world war ii 
mrs mann said previously her husband managed to elude capture 
after his plane was hit because he would have abhorred being a 
captive he once flew his burning plane all the way from germany 
to make a forced landing in england he had severe burns on nearly 
nearly 80 percent of his body 
he is a very brave man i hope somehow hes surviving but it 
has just been a dead silence a dead end a blank wall mrs mann 
said 
i havent heard anything the embassy doesnt know anything i 
havent anything to pin any hopes on only that hes a natural 
survivor and i hope hes all right 
mann lived with his wife for 40 years in west beirut he 
