<TEXT>
david levy israels new foreign minister 
worked his way from a ditchdigger to one of the highestranking 
posts ever held by a north african immigrant 
a fiery orator the moroccanborn levy 52 began his political 
career in the ranks of prime minister yitzhak shamirs rightwing 
likud bloc as a labor union boss championing the causes of the 
disadvantaged 
he advanced quickly in the party and is regarded by some as a 
political opportunist who might compromise ideology in his drive to 
succeed shamir as prime minister 
although his appointment is welcomed as a confirmation of the 
integration israels founding fathers espoused levy has little 
experience in foreign policy 
most criticized is levys scant knowledge of english which 
could hamper communication with the united states on which israel 
relies for political support and about 3 billion in annual aid 
but unlike most of his predecessors levy is fluent in arabic 
levy has a reputation as a hardliner and was one of the party 
rebels who forced shamir to accept crippling conditions to his 
initiative to hold elections in the occupied territories 
but insiders suggest levys hardline had less to do with 
ideology than with his desire to oust the polishborn shamir as 
likud leader 
in 1982 he led opposition within the likud government to 
israels protracted threeyear war in lebanon and many of the 
military moves of his party rival ariel sharon who as defense 
minister was the architect of the lebanon war 
at a news conference this week levy said his first task as 
foreign minister would be to prevent deterioration and to 
improve israels strained ties with the united states 
levys early years were immersed in the poverty that was typical 
of many of the 600000 jews from arab lands or sephardim who 
settled in israel in the 1950s and 60s 
the immigrants and their offspring now comprise more than 60 
percent of israels 45 million citizens and constitute a 
disproportionately large number of the nations poor 
in his biography levy is quoted throughout as being consumed 
with anger and resentment toward the israeli establishment because 
of the poverty and neglect he experienced in beit shean a northern 
town where he lived after immigrating at age 20 in 1957 
for israels first 30 years israel was governed by the 
centerleft labor party which was dominated by european jews or 
ashkenazim 
why do they take people who come with good will and a lot of 
love for the land of israel and grind it into sand biographer 
aryeh avinery quotes levy as saying 
after spending some time unemployed levy found work as a 
ditchdigger and construction worker 
he was first elected to the knesset or parliament at age 32 in 
1969 he won his first cabinet seat as immigration minister in 
1977 and has served as housing minister since 1979 
