of fuel that threatened to spill from the torn hull of the cruise 
ship bermuda star 
the 617foot vessel was freed sunday night from a rocky ledge 
off cape cod almost 13 hours after it strayed too close to shore 
and ran aground in dense fog 
divers found a 90by2foot tear on the ships bottom after it 
dropped anchor about 3 miles from the ledge in buzzards bay the 
