some of the demonstrators were beaten with clubs but no injuries 
or arrests were reported 
nineteen hunger strikers in university square in downtown 
bucharest backed by hundreds of other romanians have sought since 
april 22 to open a dialogue with the government they are demanding 
a freeing of the news media and a 10year ban on former communists 
holding public office 
three representatives of the hunger strikers attended talks with 
government officials monday and signed a protocol in which they 
said they would stop fasting if the government pledged in writing 
to allow private television stations to be established 
government officials told the fasters their demands came under 
