state election officials ordered a recount 
monday to determine who won the democratic nomination for governor 
because the margin in unofficial primary returns was too narrow 
the recount of the sevenway race mandated by state law will 
begin wednesday said secretary of state allen beermann he said it 
could be june 20 or later before the board reconvenes to certify 
the results 
unofficial returns of the may 15 primary showed attorney ben 
nelson in first place with 44556 votes and a 41vote lead over his 
nearest challenger bill hoppner hoppner a former aide to us 
sen bob kerrey dneb had 44515 votes 
because the margin between first and second place amounted to 
less than 1 percent of the frontrunners total it forced an 
automatic recount it had been known for several weeks that a 
recount would be ordered monday was the election boards regularly 
scheduled meeting 
the recount will be done by hand in 70 counties that still use 
paper ballots and by machine in the other 23 beermann said 
the democratic nominee will challenge incumbent gov kay orr 
the nations first republican woman elected governor who seeks a 
second fouryear term 
