<TEXT>
nestle holdings inc on monday announced a 
reorganization of several of its businesses in the united states 
including its coffee and ice cream operations 
the coffee units of nestle foods co will be joined with 
nestleowned hills bros coffee co to form nestlehills coffee co 
the new company will be based in san francisco and will include the 
brands nescafe hills bros tasters choice mjb chase and 
sanborn and sarks and zoegas 
the ice cream and dairy businesses of nestle and the carnation 
co will be folded together to form nestle ice cream co which 
will market all brands currently handled by the two separate units 
major manufacturing plants for the ice cream unit will be managed 
from los angeles 
in a third change the stouffer restaurant co will be merged 
with the stouffer hotel co to form the stouffer hospitality group 
the headquarters of the combined companies will continue to be in 
cleveland 
further steps to consolidate businesses operated by the us 
subsidiary of the big swiss foods company are under study 
specifically reorganization in the management of food services 
sales and product distribution is being studied the company said 
in a news release 
james m biggar chairman of nestle holdings said the changes 
are aimed at eliminating overlap and taking advantage of operating 
efficiencies 
nestle in the united states has been organized primarily along 
the lines of how it was acquired he said now it will seek to 
maximize efficiencies resulting from its marketing power and 
distribution strength to achieve greater focus 
</TEXT>
