korean air signed a 48 billion order monday 
for 23 boeing 747400s the thirdlargest order ever received by 
boeing co in terms of contract value 
the contract includes spare parts and training and commits 
korean air to more of boeings most sophisticated and 
highestcapacity jetliners than any other carrier except japan air 
lines jal has signed up for 40 of the worlds largest passenger 
jets 
the korean order is the third multibilliondollar purchase of 
boeing aircraft in as many weeks the others also were from asian 
air carriers a 2 billion order from the chinese government and a 
31 billion order from japan air lines 
boeing has received single orders for more planes but only two 
exceed the korean air order in dollar value an april 1989 order by 
irish aircraft leasing company gpa ltd worth 94 billion for 182 
planes and a 711 billion deal for 180 planes placed a week later 
by united airlines 
frank shrontz boeing chairman and chief executive officer told 
a news conference that the order reflects the fact that traffic 
growth in the pacific has been higher than in either the united 
states or europe 
he also said the 747400s which will be equipped to carry 392 
passengers each are best suited to meet the regions longrange 
flights and highcapacity needs 
korean air recently added longrange routes between seoul and 
moscow sydney toronto and vancouver 
korean air senior executive vice president ch cho said the 
airline also has contracts for eight other 747400s by 1994 it 
already has three in service 
cho said negotiations were under way to determine which engines 
the new planes would use he said korea produces some parts for the 
747 but the purchase is not dependent upon continued use of 
koreanmade items 
korean ambassador park tong jin said the purchase represented a 
sincere effort to reduce the countrys trade surplus with the 
united states 
boeing officials said 307 of the seattle companys 747400s have 
been ordered with 71 so far delivered to airlines around the world 
the 747400 can fly more than 8000 miles nonstop the planes 
normally sell for 116 million to 136 million each but officials 
said the korean air price reflects the estimated value of the 
dollar at the time of delivery 
